data.title: The Best Kathryn Hewton Movies & TV Shows
data.meta_description: The Best Kathryn Hewton Movies & TV Shows, as voted on by fans. Current Top 3: Freaky, Detective Pikachu, Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania
data.text:
Kathryn Newton is an American actress who has appeared in some of the best movies and TV shows of the past few years. For that reason, we're ranking them from best to worst using votes from fans like you. She made her feature film debut in Bad Teacher but was already a seasoned actress after having been in 36 episodes of Gary Unmarried. MCU fans will recognize her as Cassie Lang in Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania. She is a talented and in-demand actress and we can't wait to see what she does next. Check back for new Kathryn Newton films and television series as they are added to the list upon their release.

Vote up all your favorite movies and shows (featuring Kathryn Newton in recurring roles) to get them higher on the list. Don't hesitate to vote down the films and series you watched but didn't like so others know which ones to skip, despite being Kathryn Newton fans. Look for the Netflix, Apple TV+, Paramount+, Hulu, HBO Max, and Amazon Prime buttons below each show or movie to stream them whenever you want.

Latest additions: Lisa Frankenstein

Help shape these rankings by voting on this list of The Best Kathryn Hewton Movies & TV Shows

1

9 VOTES

Role: Millie

Seventeen-year-old Millie Kessler spends her days trying to survive high school and the cruel actions of the popular crowd. But when she becomes the latest target of the Butcher, the town's infamous serial killer, her senior year becomes the least of her worries. When the Butcher's mystical dagger causes him and Millie to magically switch bodies, the frightened teen learns she has just 24 hours to get her identity back before she looks like a middle-aged maniac forever.

Category : Film (2020)

Actors : Vince Vaughn, Kathryn Newton, Katie Finneran, Celeste O'Connor, Alan Ruck

Released : 2020

Directed by : Christopher Landon

2

8 VOTES

Detective Pikachu

Role: Lucy Stevens

In the heart of Ryme City, a metropolis brimming with human-Pokemon harmony, Tim Goodman (Justice Smith) stumbles upon Detective Pikachu (voiced by Ryan Reynolds). Plagued by amnesia but endowed with a peculiar gift - comprehensible human speech, Pikachu is an enigma wrapped in a fuzzy yellow exterior. Together they embark on a thrilling quest to unravel the mystery behind Tim's father's disappearance following a car crash. As this dynamic duo delve into clues and confront villainous Pokemon, they uncover a plot that could shatter the peaceful coexistence of the Pokemon universe. A blend of comedy, adventure, and mystery, this film offers an engaging ride for fans and newcomers alike.

Category : Film (2019)

Actors : Ryan Reynolds, Justice Jesse Smith, Kathryn Newton, Bill Nighy, Ken Watanabe

Released : 2019

Directed by : Rob Letterman

3

13 VOTES

Role: Cassie Lang

Ant-Man and the Wasp find themselves exploring the Quantum Realm, interacting with strange new creatures and embarking on an adventure that pushes them beyond the limits of what they thought was possible.

Category : Film (2023)

Actors : Paul Rudd, Evangeline Lilly, Jonathan Majors, Michelle Pfeiffer, Michael Douglas

Released : 2023

Directed by : Peyton Reed

4

12 VOTES

Role: Margaret

Two teens develop a budding romance while stuck in an endless time loop.

Category : Film (2021)

Actors : Kathryn Newton, Kyle Allen, Jermaine Harris, Anna Mikami, Josh Hamilton

Released : 2021

Directed by : Ian Samuels

5

6 VOTES

Role: Chase Rubin-Rossi

For most, teaching is an honorable profession -- except for Elizabeth (Cameron Diaz). The foul-mouthed, boozy woman can't wait to marry a rich man and quit her job, but she has to rethink her plans when her sugar daddy dumps her. Then Scott Delacorte (Justin Timberlake), a substitute teacher who's cute and rich, arrives. Elizabeth can't wait to sink her teeth into a new meal ticket, but she faces stiff competition from Amy (Lucy Punch), a popular and perky colleague.

Category : Film (2011)

Actors : Cameron Diaz, Justin Timberlake, Jason Segel, Lucy Punch, John Michael Higgins

Released : 2011

Directed by : Jake Kasdan

6

13 VOTES

Blockers

Role: Julie

Julie, Kayla and Sam are three high school seniors who make a pact to lose their virginity on prom night. Lisa, Mitchell and Hunter are three overprotective parents who flip out when they find out about their daughters' plans. They soon join forces for a wild and chaotic quest to stop the girls from sealing the deal -- no matter what the cost.

Category : Film (2018)

Actors : Leslie Mann, Ike Barinholtz, John Cena, Kathryn Newton, Geraldine Viswanathan

Released : 2018

Directed by : Kay Cannon
